statements.sql:
select sch_service_id,
sch_services.title,
sch_services.remarks,
sch_services.image,
count(sch_service_bookings.sch_service_id) as service_count,
(select (sum(sf.rating)/count(sf.id)) as avgRating
from sch_service_booking_feedback as sf join sch_service_bookings sb
on sf.sch_service_booking_id=sb.id
where sb.sch_service_id=sch_service_bookings.sch_service_id and sf.status=1) as avgRating,
(select count(sf.id) as countRating
from sch_service_booking_feedback as sf join sch_service_bookings sb
on sf.sch_service_booking_id=sb.id
where sb.sch_service_id=sch_service_bookings.sch_service_id and sf.status=1) as countRating from `sch_service_bookings` inner join `sch_services` on `sch_service_bookings`.`sch_service_id` = `sch_services`.`id` group by `sch_service_id`, `sch_services`.`title`, `sch_services`.`remarks`, `sch_services`.`image` order by service_count desc limit 10
select `name`, `image`, `rating`, `description` from `site_client_testimonials` where `status` = 1

select `sch_employees`.`full_name`, `sch_employees`.`image_url`, `hrm_departments`.`name` as `department`, `sch_employees`.`specialist` from `sch_employees` left join `hrm_departments` on `sch_employees`.`hrm_department_id` = `hrm_departments`.`id` order by `sch_employees`.`created_at` asc limit 10
select count(*) as aggregate from `sch_employees` where `status` != 3
select count(*) as aggregate from `sch_services`
select count(*) as total from `sch_service_bookings` group by `cmn_customer_id`
select count(*) as aggregate from `sch_service_bookings` where `status` = 4
select `id`, `name`, `site_menu_id`, `route`, `order` from `site_menus` where `status` = 1 order by `order` asc

select `app_name`, `logo`, `icon`, `motto`, `theam_color`, `theam_menu_color2`, `theam_hover_color`, `theam_active_color`, `facebook_link`, `youtube_link`, `twitter_link`, `instagram_link`, `about_service`, `contact_email`, `contact_phone`, `contact_web`, `address`, `background_image`, `login_background_image`, `meta_title`, `meta_description`, `meta_keywords` from `site_appearances` limit 1
select `id`, `name` from `cmn_languages` order by default_language desc
select `lang_value` from `cmn_translations` where `cmn_language_id` = 2 and `lang_key` = 'We calculate top services based on our client feedback and number of provided services.' limit 1
bindings: We calculate top services based on our client feedback and number of provided services.
